to many more generations. %0a%3c %0a%3c To address the barriers of the ageing of the fluent population and the declining appeal to children for learning Ute, the tribe has been making an effort to team up with the local school districts to offer some instruction in Ute, modeled after a similar program for the Navajo language and culture; the Ute tribe's language coordinator also works hands-on with parents who have young children to teach the language to them so they may speak it fluently (3). There has also been (still!) ongoing work to create a dictionary for the language (4), which has been very successful thanks to a joint collaboration with tribal members, leadership, and academics, as well as The Language Conservancy. The website is modern, responsive, and represents a serious effort to use documentation as a driving force to preserving the language as it exists now, for use as a resource in the above efforts to ensure it passes on to more generations.%0a%3c %0a%3c ----------%0a%3c 1: https://www.endangeredlanguages.com/lang/2965%0a%3c 2: https://www.ethnologue.com/size-and-vitality/ute%0a%3c 3: https://www.deseret.com/2007/4/22/20014405/utes-fear-their-language-could-disappear%0a%3c 4: https://dictionary.utelanguage.org/Acknowledgements%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!C